Gâteau Infiniment Citron: The Study of Acidity
Inspired by the "Infiniment" (Infinitely) series by Pierre Hermé, this concept focuses on exploring a single ingredient through multiple textures and intensities.59
Architectural Composition
Lemon Elements: It typically includes a lemon sponge soaked in lemon syrup, a lemon marmalade (using the zest for bitterness), a lemon cream (curd or mousse), and often a lemon jelly or glaze.60
Sensory Analysis and Taste Profile
This gâteau is for the acid-hound. It explores the full spectrum of the lemon: the sour juice, the aromatic oil of the zest, and the controlled bitterness of the pith. It is a palate-cleansing, vibrant dessert that energizes the mouth.
